JOHANNESBURG - The Empangeni Regional Court in KwaZulu-Natal has convicted and sentenced a 53-year-old man to two life sentences for raping his 13-year-old daughter five years ago. Police said the man was found guilty after the magistrate heard how he had repeatedly raped his daughter in 2013. READ: Gang-raped 13-year-old girl pregnant with twins "In February 2013, the victim was at her father’s homestead at Matshana area, Empangeni when she was called by her father to his bedroom.  She was raped by her father and she reported the matter to her stepmother, who was not at home on that day. "The local police were called and a case of rape was opened at Empangeni police station. The docket was transferred to Empangeni Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences unit for further investigation. After thorough investigation, the accused was arrested and charged with rape," police said. READ: Woman who killed daughter's alleged rapist won't be charged The KwaZulu-Natal acting provincial commissioner, Major General Bheki Langa, welcomed the sentence and said it would serve as a warning to would-be criminals who intentionally abuse children. eNCA